            <h2 id="lon">How to Apply for Education Loan</h2>
            <p>To apply for an education loan, visit the <a href="https://www.vidyalakshmi.co.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">VIDYALAKSHMI portal</a> and follow the instructions provided. Be sure to check the eligibility criteria and required documents before applying.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2 id="lon">If Your Father's Credit Score is Poor</h2>
            <p>Some bankers may outright reject your application due to your father's poor credit score. However, some may string you along for months, making you wait for hours at the bank. For those facing such challenges, consider filing a complaint with the National Consumer Helpline (NCH) if you believe you're being unfairly treated. You may need to provide details of your loan application process, including your loan ID and dates of interactions.</p>
            <p>Remember, there are options available even in the face of adversity. Don't hesitate to explore them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section" >
            <h2 id="lon">Stuck in Loan Limbo for Months?</h2>
            <p>If you find yourself stuck in the loan approval process for months without any progress, don't lose hope. follow this step</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2 id="lone">Step 1: Informing the Loan Manager</h2>
            <p>Step 1 requires you to inform the loan manager that if they refuse to grant you the loan, you will have no choice but to take legal action.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2 id="lone">Step 2: Proceeding with VIDYALAKSHMI Portal</h2>
            <p>If the manager remains uncooperative, politely request them to provide you with the loan ID obtained from the VIDYALAKSHMI portal. Once received, proceed to contact the National Consumer Helpline (NCH).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2 id="lone">Step 3: Providing Details to NCH</h2>
            <p>Step 3 involves providing all necessary details, including your loan ID and other relevant information such as the duration of the delay and the behavior of the bankers, to the National Consumer Helpline (NCH).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2 id="lone">Step 4: Firmly Standing by Your Complaint</h2>
            <p>Upon filing the complaint, expect a call from your bank manager within one day. They may politely request you to withdraw your complaint, but it's important to stand firm. It's likely that 70% to 80% of the time, your loan will be sanctioned after this process.</p>
